review_blob: Nice fresh hazy orange look with piney aroma. Bitter taste of amarillo hops, citrus, yeast. Nice beer and quite refreshing.
[Bottle from my romanian colleque bought in Transsylvania.] Average good industrial beer with notes of hay, bread, grass and with a medium body.

[Bottle bought in Bazar Fyn, Odense.] Real poison. I think this bottle must have been lagered for too long time in a hot corner of this Yugo-shop. Notes of alcohol, grain, straw and bad old hops. According to the other ratings this beer deserves another test.

[Bottle bought in Vaduz, Liechtenstrin at a petrolstation, july 2011.] The best of the 3 lnder. Nothing special, but it worked well with clear yellow look and pale white head and notes of straw and low grass.
All I can say is that I love IPAs and indeed Meantimes is a keen one with notes of floral, grass, caramel, citrus and hops in the finish. Great!
Aroma and flavor of caramel, bread, butterscotch, nuts, vanilla  and foam makes this beer a good favorite

[Tasted at rsted in november 2010.] Wow man. What a beer. At that low alc. it must be a must-brew for an athletic as me. I cannot stand much volume, and prefor beers like thisone. Great notes of  citrus, herbs, floral, grass and all in heavy doses. Some of us thought it was 12 %. If possible Ill brew it next time!
Bottle @ BeerBiker/Scheffels 100 countries celebration week (long time ago). In the heat, it could be a nice easy drinkable beer. Could add more hops and it would be an okay beachsnifter!
Bottle @ BeerBiker/Scheffels 100 countries celebration week (long time ago). Bottle from Ren bought in Beirut. Nice average beer with notes of caramel, malt, bread and with a fine brown coulour.

Bottle @ BeerBiker/Scheffels 100 countries celebration week (long time ago)
Surprise, surprise. Not that bad a beer from Africa. Notes of caramel, hay, clear straw and it could be good for meat balls in Nairobi or Zanzibar!

beer_brewer_name: Socit Frigorifique et Brasserie de Tunis (SFBT)
review_blob:
Bottle @ BeerBiker/Scheffels 100 countries celebration week (long time ago)
Bottle from Vicki bought in Tunesia, after a long fight. My first impression was holy shit and gave me the thoughts of hay, wet grass, poison and very hot sweaty skin.

[On tour with svoger, svogergylp and adenila.] After having sampled 7 bottles from the single hop collection, this afternoon, we finished it with this 10, which in a remarkable way did not dizzied our smell-senses. Very wellbalanced and we decided that we could note the nelson sauvin.

[On tour with svoger, svogergylp and adenila.] Bought in Berlin. Country #96. Not that bad for a beer from the deepest desertplace on earth. Pilsnernotes, straw, caramel, slight hops and slowly drinkable.

[On tour with svoger, svogergylp and adenila.] Bought in Berlin. Country-beer #95. Another pilsner from middle-east, which I had expects for could be great after a long bikeride, but it all flew out of my mouth with all those nonhoppy notes. Only caramel, straw and brown rusty metal.

# 1400. Sampled draught at Mikkeller Bar. Some of the best ever sampled. Enormous welldosed amounts of hops and it must be a great mans work making this beer drinkable with that IBU. Notes of citrus, floral, caramel, leaves and a beer that must be resampled every day for a long time.

[On tour with svoger, svogergylp and adenila.] Bought in Berlin. Another country-ticker-beer #94 from hell. True international pilsnerstyle and nothing to come for. Notes of metal, caramel and old straw.

Very great beer indeed. Not that quite different from the origin, but smoother and with a high drinkable palate with many notes like some smoke, whisky, oak , leather, roasted coffee, this special beergeek taste and just lovely and lordy.

Bottle @ Odense Tasting, Feb 2010. I almost swallowed the first sips , because I thought it wasnt 32 %, but my throat told me the truth. No head and with a wonderful look. Notes of cask, port, oak, medicine, wood, caramel, brandy, raisin, coffee, licorice and tar. Its own special taste, maybe a mix of whisky and barley wine. Great experience....and remember to see the video!

[Bottle from Thorstein bought in Medellin, Colombia.]Bottle @ Odense Tasting, Feb 2010. This is not the perfect beer as mentioned above. Poisoned and metal mixed with drugs from the lab around the corner must have been the result of this "beer".
[Can from Kjell bought in Cairo.] Can @ Odense Tasting, Feb 2010. Noisy brew, but it was the best "overseas" beer that eve. Watery and corny.
UPDATED: JUN 20, 2011

Thanks to Janni & Rasmus for bringing this can all the way from Mauritius during their honeymoon. Odense Prestige tasting at Jens. Clear offyellow look with fast head and aroma/flavor of corn, malt, good metal, some weak hops and not bad for an international pilsner if tasted very cold close to 0 degrees Celcius.

[On tap - Blindtasting at Pegasus.] First impression was Poperinge Hommelbier and I did not accept, that is was a belgo x-mas beer, due to the lack of spices. Lots of hops and heavy fruits in the triple way. Some dust and horse. Fresh and nice!
[Bottled, ...with Jan.] Clear light amber. Notes of slight fruits, sweet caramel, malt and with some weak hop watery finish.

Bottle. Not that bad, but also not mindblowing. I must say, that it is a hard mans job brewing a great schwarzbier. There are many, and they are not that bad, but getting closer to the Kstritzer will take some time. Maybe Im wrong, but Vestfyen will not be the preferable.
[On tap at Carlsens with Bo.] Not that bad and quite refreshing although its 7 %. Good malt dose and some dusty flavor added with weak fruits, caramel and low carbonation. Ok brew from Assens!
[On tap at Carlsens with Bo.] Great haze look and wonderful fluffy lasting head. Pines, grass, grapes, pills, citrus, amounthops, malt and a good felling of eating lawn for breakfast.

beer_brewer_name: Bernard Family Brewery / Rodinn pivovar Bernard
review_blob: [Gift from Mia, bought on location.] Nice fullbodied dunkel with notes of smoke and a great aroma of fullfillness. Cream, malt, smoke, salami, bacon, chocs, dust and mmmmmmmmmm. To be resampled!
beer_name: Bernard ern Lek 12 / Bernard Dark Lager

review_blob: [Sampled at the MS-Swamp-lovers gathering.] This is honey, but also a thin beer, a bit watery. Look of thin amber and fast head. Flowery and honey, medium fullness. Light drinkable, but its okay for sipping in the medium hot autumn weather.

[Sampled at the MS-Swamp-lovers gathering.] Clear amber look and small head. Aroma of pines needles, needlewood, like old danish klosterbeer brewed with needles instead of hops. Nice weelbalanced flavor, where its never too much with the doses. Good brew.
[Sampled at the MS-Swamp-lovers gathering.] Great surprise from Haderslev. Did not expect that, but the cascade is wellbalanced in normal doses and could do a very great job on tap in the summertime.
[Sampled at the MS-Swamp-lovers gathering.] This is true banana flavor with nut, caramel, sweetmaltness and with and ok interesting look.

[Bought at UTO-beer, Borough Market, London.] A good thirstquencher for autumn-times. Not that christmas-sweet-like as the belgian ones, but  more like an original ale added with spices, but a goodone is it indeed. Brown look with offw. head and notes of weak spices as cardamomme, cinnamon, some wood. Light and easy drinkable.
beer_name: Anchor Our Special Ale (2005 and later)

review_blob: [Bought at UTO-beer, Borough Market, London.] Acid pale-yellow look with fluffy offwhite head. Aroflavor of grapefruit, real grapes (muscat maybe), sure acid, dryness, souryeast, grapepeel ending up with a beautiful finish. Fantastic beer!
[Sampled at fynsk dyreskue.] An okay beer with remarkable notes of marble. Amber look with fast head with caramel, some sweetness and nutty oil.

[Bottle from Bjarne.] A true bomb, which exploded all over the kids table to the vejfest. More like an belgian abbey ale with all those fruitnotes, caramel, dried berries, sweetness and heavy alcohol percentage. Good surprise, Bjarne!

[Sampled in Svaneke at svogers summerhouse.] Boring look, but the hops turned it in another direction. Pilsnerlook and offwhite head. Notes of citrus, caramel, freshness and good american pale hops. Drinkable for hours.

[Proudly brought all the way on bike from Belgium by svoger.] Lots of wheat-look-a-like notes, fruits, haze blond look with an explosive headbomb, refreshing, yeasty, surprisingly easy drinkable despite the 8.5 %. Short finish.

[Sampled with Ren....and CKlaus north of Gilleleje.] Haze yellowamber with fast head and good notes of complex citric and acid elements in a great combination. Vinegar, leather, horseblanket, barnyard, earthy, woody, all mixes together  to an indeed great brew. WOW
Urine look with plain head. Notes of pebberchili and vegetable-garbage and lots of water. Not that mindblowing, but I dont know if it could be okay in the jungle!?
Sodapop for the masses. The cider-generation breaks through these days. Hopefully they will not destroy our beerrevolution. But an okay thirstquencher for the first two sips.

[Sampled with the duo Svoger & Svogergylp at DE, Valby, 2009.] Amazing how Eddie keeps on brewing wellbalanced beers. A perfect tapasbeer with detectable chili. Good and enjoyable when its cold on a hot summerday.

[Sampled with the duo Svoger & Svogergylp at DE, Valby, 2009.] Barleywine for everybody. In my eyes many barleywines are too much challenging or just not good enough, although I like the style. Thisone is great with mellow mouthfeel and a very wellbalanced mix of flavors. Notes of warming alcohol. dried fruits, caramel, positive bitterness, port, fullfillness. All very welldone. My next speech will be with thisone!

[Sampled with the duo Svoger & Svogergylp at DE, Valby, 2009.] Wow, what an entry to Valby 2009. First sample and I flew direct to Nirvarna. Haze orange and fast head. Very refreshing lambic/saison notes of citrus, horseblanket, grapefruit, lemon, bretts, dryness and freshness in perfect balance, yeah like an imp. Orval as Scheffel mentions. My first notes were 10-5-10-5-20, but I downdosed it a bit!

[Sampled with the duo Svoger & Svogergylp at DE, Valby, 2009.] Deep red brew with fast offwhite head. Notes of true heavy sweet hops with caramel. More notes of warming alcohol, fat sweetness, weak whisky-notes, fullbodied and with a complex aftertaste.

[Sampled with the duo Svoger & Svogergylp at DE, Valby, 2009.] My only note from this experince was: POISON

....hmmmmmmmmm

[Sampled with the duo Svoger & Svogergylp at DE, Valby, 2009.] Fantastic brew with smoothy porterbody added with licorice, smoke, spices like chili, almost no chocolate, coffee and indeed a great brew...I would like to live in Helsinge. Move soon!!!

[Sampled with the duo Svoger & Svogergylp at DE, Valby, 2009.] I like hops especially after 80 km, then I swallowed it all in a split-second. Notes of flowerhops, smoothsness, caramel, leather. A true thirstquencher!

[Sampled with the duo Svoger & Svogergylp at DE, Valby, 2009.] Another great funny beer. Combinationstyles must be the new word. Black with many citric-hops dominated with roast, chocolate, but also some easy-swallow feeling in this beer!

[Sampled with the duo Svoger & Svogergylp at DE, Valby, 2009.] Very black brew with asphalt notes. Strange combination, but ok. Dominating hops and fullbodied, roast and a long finish of hops, chai and tar.
